reviewText:
A (poor) mix of Mass Effect gameplay with XCom universe

Playing this game wasn't a horrible experiece, but wasn't a good one eighter.
The only really good thing I can say about it is that it really captures the spirit of the Cold War times.

-Buggy: at least 3 times I had to reload a chackpoint because the trigger wouldn't kick in;
-Bad save system based on checkpoints;
-Moral decision have almost null impact in the game (even at the ending where it SEEMS to change something). The truth is that this is a linear on the tracks game" masked as more free decision thing.
-There is very low customization options and there is no effort to create an emotional attachment with the characters;
-The IA is pretty terrible

hoursPlayed:
 running and shooting is much more "fluid" than in The Bureau XCOM;
-Short list of sidequest with little to no meaning.

I could list some other things. I admit it
